text: Lebyazhye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Obrastsovo-Travinsky Selsoviet, Kamyzyaksky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 732 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 19 km SSE from Kamyzyak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kamyzyaksky District
title: Lebyazhye, Kamyzyaksky District, Astrakhan Oblast
